, \"to\": 411}, {\"ngram\": \"a former deputy prime minister\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 445}, {\"ngram\": \"finance minister\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 466}, {\"ngram\": \"professor\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"political economy\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 508}, {\"ngram\": \"the Belt and Road School\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 599}, {\"ngram\": \"the books\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 657}, {\"ngram\": \"the Future\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 679}, {\"ngram\": \"Globalization\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 696}, {\"ngram\": \"The Political Economy\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 719}, {\"ngram\": \"China's Rise\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 735}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Global Consequences\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"Ukraine\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 813}, {\"ngram\": \"The Economics\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 828}, {\"ngram\": \"Politics\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 841}, {\"ngram\": \"the Second Cold War\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 864}, {\"ngram\": \"(Springer\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2023).\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The article reflects the author's opinions and not necessarily the views of CGTN.\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The article\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 896}, {\"ngram\": \"the author's opinions\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 927}, {\"ngram\": \"not necessarily the views\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 957}, {\"ngram\": \"CGTN\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International relations are deteriorating, mutual mistrust between states is growing, the cold-war atmosphere is intensifying, and bloody conflicts are taking place, especially in Ukraine and the Gaza Strip.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1148, \"end\": 1155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7957066498897164e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 1164, \"end\": 1174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3605326320554344e-15, \"text\": \"Gaza Strip\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"International relations\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 991}, {\"ngram\": \"mutual mistrust\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1026}, {\"ngram\": \"states\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1041}, {\"ngram\": \"the cold-war atmosphere\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"bloody conflicts\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By no means it has to be that way, and yet it is and will be for some time to come.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1259, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no means\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1187}, {\"ngram\": \"that way\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1209}, {\"ngram\": \"some time\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No one knows for how long.\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No one\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1266}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The drama of the situation lies in the fact that in various countries the forces pushing for clashes rather than peaceful dialogue tend to be more influential.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The drama\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1297}, {\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1314}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1331}, {\"ngram\": \"various countries\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1357}, {\"ngram\": \"the forces\", \"from\": 1358, \"to\": 1368}, {\"ngram\": \"clashes\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1388}, {\"ngram\": \"peaceful dialogue\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1418}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pro-war pressure groups in certain Western countries are more powerful than peaceful political circles.\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1484, \"end\": 1491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.635279170798391e-14, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pro-war pressure groups\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1471}, {\"ngram\": \"peaceful political circles\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the stupidest sentences in history is being thoughtlessly promoted: If you want peace, get ready for war.\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1665, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the stupidest sentences\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1583}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1594}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1645}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1664}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, no; if one desires peace, one must get ready for it rather than spend a fortune to arm oneself to the teeth, which can be knocked out by others arming themselves.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1835, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1697}, {\"ngram\": \"one\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"a fortune\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1752}, {\"ngram\": \"oneself\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1767}, {\"ngram\": \"the teeth\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1780}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1816}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, even a minor incident can lead to a major disaster.\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1894, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"even a minor incident\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1864}, {\"ngram\": \"a major disaster\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But still, it is not too late.\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For every action, there is a reaction.\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1965, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every action\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1943}, {\"ngram\": \"a reaction\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 1964}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The spiral of military spending is getting momentum.\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 2018, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The spiral\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 1976}, {\"ngram\": \"military spending\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 1997}, {\"ngram\": \"momentum\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2017}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2023, the world spent a record $2.4 trillion on armaments, 6.8 percent more than in the previous year, according to the Stockholm International Peace Research Institute (SIPRI).\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2142, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stockholm International Peace Research Institute (SIPRI)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2037}, {\"ngram\": \"a record\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2052}, {\"ngram\": \"armaments\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2079}, {\"ngram\": \"the previous year\", \"from\": 2106, \"to\": 2123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world military burden, which is defined as military spending as a percentage of global GDP, increased to 2.3 percent in 2023.\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The world military burden\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2225}, {\"ngram\": \"military spending\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2264}, {\"ngram\": \"a percentage\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2280}, {\"ngram\": \"global GDP\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"2.3 percent\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, there is not enough money for healthcare and education, infrastructure development, and combating disastrous global warming, not to mention culture and science.\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2501, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"enough money\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2366}, {\"ngram\": \"healthcare\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"education\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2395}, {\"ngram\": \"infrastructure development\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2423}, {\"ngram\": \"disastrous global warming\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2488}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is obvious that because of various conflicts of ideas and interests, maintaining security requires keeping a balance of power.\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2632, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"various conflicts\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2550}, {\"ngram\": \"ideas\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2559}, {\"ngram\": \"interests\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2573}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 2587, \"to\": 2595}, {\"ngram\": \"a balance\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2622}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2631}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the trick is to achieve such a desired state at the lowest possible cost, not with ever greater outlays.\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the trick\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2646}, {\"ngram\": \"such a desired state\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2681}, {\"ngram\": \"the lowest possible cost\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2709}, {\"ngram\": \"ever greater outlays\", \"from\": 2720, \"to\": 2740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, the latter is the case in several countries, starting from the NATO members grandly celebrating the bloc's 75th anniversary.\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2820, \"end\": 2824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5247188923642576e-14, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2779}, {\"ngram\": \"several countries\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 2800}, {\"ngram\": \"the bloc's 75th anniversary\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 2880}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NATO Secretary-General Jens Stoltenberg announced that in 2024, 23 out of the 32 total member countries will meet or exceed the target of spending at least 2 percent of GDP on defense.\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 3066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2882, \"end\": 2886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5247188923642576e-14, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}, {\"begin\": 2905, \"end\": 2921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jens_Stoltenberg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jens Stoltenberg\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jens_Stoltenberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jens_Stoltenberg\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 32 total member countries\", \"from\": 2956, \"to\": 2985}, {\"ngram\": \"the target\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3016}, {\"ngram\": \"spending\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3028}, {\"ngram\": \"at least 2 percent\", \"from\": 3029, \"to\": 3047}, {\"ngram\": \"GDP\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3054}, {\"ngram\": \"defense\", \"from\": 3058, \"to\": 3065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The biggest arms spender is the U.S. with $916 billion.\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3123, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The biggest arms spender\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3092}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is no wonder that their budget deficit is approaching 7 percent of GDP, and massive public debt is growing, approaching 100 percent of GDP, threatening to destabilize its economy.\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3306, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no wonder\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3139}, {\"ngram\": \"their budget deficit\", \"from\": 3145, \"to\": 3165}, {\"ngram\": \"7 percent\", \"from\": 3181, \"to\": 3190}, {\"ngram\": \"GDP\", \"from\": 3194, \"to\": 3197}, {\"ngram\": \"massive public debt\", \"from\": 3203, \"to\": 3222}, {\"ngram\": \"100 percent\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3258}, {\"ngram\": \"GDP\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3265}, {\"ngram\": \"its economy\", \"from\": 3294, \"to\": 3305}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American industrial-military lobby, together with the parties they finance and the corrupt media, is so strong that peaceful voices are effectively silenced.\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3311, \"end\": 3319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.332003051988776e-19, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the parties\", \"from\": 3361, \"to\": 3372}, {\"ngram\": \"the corrupt media\", \"from\": 3390, \"to\": 3407}, {\"ngram\": \"peaceful voices\", \"from\": 3427, \"to\": 3442}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than half of the global military spending \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 $1.3 trillion \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 is made by NATO.\", \"from\": 3470, \"to\": 3555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3550, \"end\": 3554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5247188923642576e-14, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"More than half\", \"from\": 3470, \"to\": 3484}, {\"ngram\": \"the global military spending\", \"from\": 3488, \"to\": 3516}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093\", \"from\": 3535, \"to\": 3538}]}, {\"sentence\": \"European member states share 28 percent of these costs, in total spending over three times more than Russia, which allocated the equivalent of only $109 billion, equivalent to 5.9 percent of its GDP.\", \"from\": 3556, \"to\": 3755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3657, \"end\": 3663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.757301517308286e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"European member states\", \"from\": 3556, \"to\": 3578}, {\"ngram\": \"28 percent\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 3595}, {\"ngram\": \"these costs\", \"from\": 3599, \"to\": 3610}, {\"ngram\": \"total spending\", \"from\": 3615, \"to\": 3629}, {\"ngram\": \"the equivalent\", \"from\": 3681, \"to\": 3695}, {\"ngram\": \"5.9 percent\", \"from\": 3732, \"to\": 3743}, {\"ngram\": \"its GDP\", \"from\": 3747, \"to\": 3754}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though taking the purchasing power parity into account it is the equivalent of almost $400 billion, according to estimates by SIPRI, it is still a third less than the expenditures of the European NATO countries.\", \"from\": 3756, \"to\": 3967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3882, \"end\": 3887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SIPRI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\"}, {\"begin\": 3952, \"end\": 3956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5247188923642576e-14, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the purchasing power parity\", \"from\": 3770, \"to\": 3797}, {\"ngram\": \"account\", \"from\": 3803, \"to\": 3810}, {\"ngram\": \"the equivalent\", \"from\": 3817, \"to\": 3831}, {\"ngram\": \"estimates\", \"from\": 3869, \"to\": 3878}, {\"ngram\": \"the expenditures\", \"from\": 3919, \"to\": 3935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If only the members of the European Union are considered, their aggregated military budgets still exceed that of Russia.\", \"from\": 3968, \"to\": 4088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4004, \"end\": 4009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0127316007773654e-23, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4081, \"end\": 4087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.757301517308286e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only the members\", \"from\": 3971, \"to\": 3987}, {\"ngram\": \"their aggregated military budgets\", \"from\": 4026, \"to\": 4059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Balance of power is not about further increasing the spending of the member states or creating a special EU military fund \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 though there are suggestions of going into debt of several hundred billion euros for this purpose \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 but about making better use of the already vast resources allocated to the military, i.e.\", \"from\": 4090, \"to\": 