22.\", \"from\": 4656, \"to\": 4807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4714, \"end\": 4721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7957066498897164e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 4775, \"end\": 4779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyiv\", \"score\": 0.9999999957608452, \"rank\": 4.238971597210112e-09, \"text\": \"Kyiv\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyiv\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyiv\"}, {\"begin\": 4781, \"end\": 4788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7957066498897164e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A new consignment\", \"from\": 4656, \"to\": 4673}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. security assistance\", \"from\": 4677, \"to\": 4701}, {\"ngram\": \"the Boryspil International Airport\", \"from\": 4737, \"to\": 4771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/VCG Does it make us safer?\", \"from\": 4808, \"to\": 4836, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 4828}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if such is the conclusion drawn from an opinion survey, we must be aware that public view is deeply manipulated through the media narrative.\", \"from\": 4837, \"to\": 4982, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the conclusion\", \"from\": 4853, \"to\": 4867}, {\"ngram\": \"an opinion survey\", \"from\": 4879, \"to\": 4896}, {\"ngram\": \"public view\", \"from\": 4920, \"to\": 4931}, {\"ngram\": \"the media narrative\", \"from\": 4962, \"to\": 4981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People must first be frightened by the specter of the enemy.\", \"from\": 4983, \"to\": 5043, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"People\", \"from\": 4983, \"to\": 4989}, {\"ngram\": \"the specter\", \"from\": 5018, \"to\": 5029}, {\"ngram\": \"the enemy\", \"from\": 5033, \"to\": 5042}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then it is easier to distract them from the failures of the policies unable to effectively address other pressing problems.\", \"from\": 5044, \"to\": 5167, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the failures\", \"from\": 5084, \"to\": 5096}, {\"ngram\": \"the policies\", \"from\": 5100, \"to\": 5112}, {\"ngram\": \"other pressing problems\", \"from\": 5143, \"to\": 5166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So the psychological terror of societies continues.\", \"from\": 5168, \"to\": 5219, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the psychological terror\", \"from\": 5171, \"to\": 5195}, {\"ngram\": \"societies\", \"from\": 5199, \"to\": 5208}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Arousing anxiety is also an instrument used to increase the profits of already lucrative businesses.\", \"from\": 5221, \"to\": 5321, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anxiety\", \"from\": 5230, \"to\": 5237}, {\"ngram\": \"an instrument\", \"from\": 5246, \"to\": 5259}, {\"ngram\": \"the profits\", \"from\": 5277, \"to\": 5288}, {\"ngram\": \"already lucrative businesses\", \"from\": 5292, \"to\": 5320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the five years of 2019-2023, compared to the 2014-2018 period, the share of United States arms exports in total global exports increased from 34 percent to 42 percent.\", \"from\": 5322, \"to\": 5496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5405, \"end\": 5418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998634809407859, \"rank\": 0.00013653769899656058, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the five years\", \"from\": 5329, \"to\": 5343}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2014-2018 period\", \"from\": 5370, \"to\": 5390}, {\"ngram\": \"the share\", \"from\": 5392, \"to\": 5401}, {\"ngram\": \"total global exports\", \"from\": 5435, \"to\": 5455}, {\"ngram\": \"34 percent\", \"from\": 5471, \"to\": 5481}, {\"ngram\": \"42 percent\", \"from\": 5485, \"to\": 5495}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During that time, the U.S. supplied arms to 107 countries.\", \"from\": 5497, \"to\": 5555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that time\", \"from\": 5504, \"to\": 5513}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 5515, \"to\": 5523}, {\"ngram\": \"arms\", \"from\": 5533, \"to\": 5537}, {\"ngram\": \"107 countries\", \"from\": 5541, \"to\": 5554}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the situation becomes more complicated, all kinds of scenarios for the evolution of the situation on the political and war fronts are being plotted.\", \"from\": 5557, \"to\": 5708, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 5560, \"to\": 5573}, {\"ngram\": \"all kinds\", \"from\": 5600, \"to\": 5609}, {\"ngram\": \"scenarios\", \"from\": 5613, \"to\": 5622}, {\"ngram\": \"the evolution\", \"from\": 5627, \"to\": 5640}, {\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 5644, \"to\": 5657}, {\"ngram\": \"the political and war fronts\", \"from\": 5661, \"to\": 5689}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The conflict between Russia and Ukraine is being prolonged because neither side is willing to make concessions, without which it will be impossible to reach a peaceful compromise.\", \"from\": 5709, \"to\": 5888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5730, \"end\": 5736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.757301517308286e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 5741, \"end\": 5748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7957066498897164e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The conflict\", \"from\": 5709, \"to\": 5721}, {\"ngram\": \"neither side\", \"from\": 5776, \"to\": 5788}, {\"ngram\": \"concessions\", \"from\": 5808, \"to\": 5819}, {\"ngram\": \"a peaceful compromise\", \"from\": 5866, \"to\": 5887}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The conflict persists because it is no longer a secret that the West is using it as an instrument to weaken Russia not only as revenge for its \\\"special military operation\\\" in Ukraine, but in the context of ongoing tectonic geopolitical changes.\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 6134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5998, \"end\": 6004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.757301517308286e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 6065, \"end\": 6072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7957066498897164e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The conflict\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 5902}, {\"ngram\": \"a secret\", \"from\": 5936, \"to\": 5944}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 5950, \"to\": 5958}, {\"ngram\": \"an instrument\", \"from\": 5974, \"to\": 5987}, {\"ngram\": \"revenge\", \"from\": 6017, \"to\": 6024}, {\"ngram\": \"its \\\"special military operation\", \"from\": 6029, \"to\": 6060}, {\"ngram\": \"the context\", \"from\": 6081, \"to\": 6092}, {\"ngram\": \"ongoing tectonic geopolitical changes\", \"from\": 6096, \"to\": 6133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hence, this war must be continued, exhausting Russian human and material resources.\", \"from\": 6135, \"to\": 6218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6181, \"end\": 6188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9900917128351188, \"rank\": 0.01000639498229699, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this war\", \"from\": 6142, \"to\": 6150}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sanctions were not imposed all at once, with devastating effect, but have been imposed in successive limited portions (the EU introduced 14 such bans during the 28 months of the war).\", \"from\": 6219, \"to\": 6402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6342, \"end\": 6344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7750996353518245e-15, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sanctions\", \"from\": 6219, \"to\": 6228}, {\"ngram\": \"devastating effect\", \"from\": 6264, \"to\": 6282}, {\"ngram\": \"successive limited portions\", \"from\": 6309, \"to\": 6336}, {\"ngram\": \"14 such bans\", \"from\": 6356, \"to\": 6368}, {\"ngram\": \"the 28 months\", \"from\": 6376, \"to\": 6389}, {\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 6393, \"to\": 6400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aid to Ukraine is also being provided gradually, in ineffective installments.\", \"from\": 6404, \"to\": 6481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6411, \"end\": 6418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7957066498897164e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ineffective installments\", \"from\": 6456, \"to\": 6480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Previously, there was no consent to deliver state-of-the-art tanks or F-16 fighters, but now they are being sent, as well as long-range missiles capable of attacking targets on Russian territory.\", \"from\": 6482, \"to\": 6677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6659, \"end\": 6666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9900917128351188, \"rank\": 0.01000639498229699, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no consent\", \"from\": 6504, \"to\": 6514}, {\"ngram\": \"the-art\", \"from\": 6535, \"to\": 6542}, {\"ngram\": \"F-16 fighters\", \"from\": 6552, \"to\": 6565}, {\"ngram\": \"long-range missiles\", \"from\": 6607, \"to\": 6626}, {\"ngram\": \"targets\", \"from\": 6648, \"to\": 6655}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Certain NATO countries are even considering sending their soldiers to Ukraine.\", \"from\": 6678, \"to\": 6756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6686, \"end\": 6690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5247188923642576e-14, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}, {\"begin\": 6748, \"end\": 6755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7957066498897164e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their soldiers\", \"from\": 6730, \"to\": 6744}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This prolongs the armed conflict and constitutes a threat that the crisis will escalate.\", \"from\": 6757, \"to\": 6845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the armed conflict\", \"from\": 6771, \"to\": 6789}, {\"ngram\": \"a threat\", \"from\": 6806, \"to\": 6814}, {\"ngram\": \"the crisis\", \"from\": 6820, \"to\": 6830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not the way.\", \"from\": 6847, \"to\": 6867, \"entities\": [], \"nou